text:
18/02/24
Char siew is not bad but the wantons are just normal. The Hong Kong-style noodle is springy and chewy which is very nice.
One of the best char siew rice at $3.50. More value for money than the noodles which cost around $4.50 at the noodle stall in the same coffeeshop
Taste is ok. But for the price of $8, portion is very small. Expensive
